parameters.name: EndpointName
parameters.description: The name of the DevEndpoint to be updated.

parameters.name: AddPublicKeys
parameters.description: The list of public keys for the DevEndpoint to use. (string) ---

parameters.name: DeletePublicKeys
parameters.description: The list of public keys to be deleted from the DevEndpoint. (string) ---

parameters.name: CustomLibraries
parameters.description: Custom Python or Java libraries to be loaded in the DevEndpoint. ExtraPythonLibsS3Path (string) --- The paths to one or more Python libraries in an Amazon Simple Storage Service (Amazon S3) bucket that should be loaded in your DevEndpoint. Multiple values must be complete paths separated by a comma. ExtraJarsS3Path (string) --- The path to one or more Java .jar files in an S3 bucket that should be loaded in your DevEndpoint.

nested_params.name: ExtraPythonLibsS3Path
nested_params.description: The paths to one or more Python libraries in an Amazon Simple Storage Service (Amazon S3) bucket that should be loaded in your DevEndpoint. Multiple values must be complete paths separated by a comma.

nested_params.name: ExtraJarsS3Path
nested_params.description: The path to one or more Java .jar files in an S3 bucket that should be loaded in your DevEndpoint.

parameters.name: DeleteArguments
parameters.description: The list of argument keys to be deleted from the map of arguments used to configure the DevEndpoint. (string) ---

parameters.name: AddArguments
parameters.description: The map of arguments to add the map of arguments used to configure the DevEndpoint. Valid arguments are: "--enable-glue-datacatalog": "" You can specify a version of Python support for development endpoints by using the Arguments parameter in the CreateDevEndpoint or UpdateDevEndpoint APIs. If no arguments are provided, the version defaults to Python 2. (string) --- (string) ---
